            </etym>
            <note anchored="true">Cf.
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">AC I 176ab</bibl>;
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Levy I 123ab</bibl>;
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Krauss, LW II 122ab</bibl>;
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Jastrow I 91b</bibl>. Frequently corr. <term xml:lang="jpa">אסטרוגוליא</term>
               <term xml:lang="fjb">ʾsṭrwgwlyʾ</term>
               <term xml:lang="rabbinic">a(i)sṭrogoliaʾ</term>. Levy and Jastrow consider the reading <term xml:lang="jpa">אסטרולוגין</term>
               <term xml:lang="fjb">ʾsṭrwlwgyn</term>
               <term xml:lang="rabbinic">a(i)sṭrologin</term> in Vat 1 (and other) for GenR 85,2 as pl., but cf. Krauss. For Syr. <term xml:lang="syc">ܐܣܛܪܘܠܘܓܝܐ</term>
               <term xml:lang="fjb">ʾsṭrwlogyʾ</term> cf.
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Sokoloff, SL 70b</bibl>. Cf.
      <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">אסטרולוג</ref>
            </note>
